#. <section class="sutta" id="sn47.95-104"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn47.95-104:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 47"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 47"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.95-104:0.2"
msgid "10. Oghavagga"
msgstr "10. Floods"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn47.95-104:0.3"
msgid "95–​104. Uddhambhāgiyādisutta"
msgstr "95–​104. Higher Fetters, Etc."

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.192"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn47.95-104:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, uddhambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni."
msgstr ""
"(To be expanded as in SN 45.171–179, with the following as the final "
"discourse.) “Mendicants, there are five higher fetters."

msgctxt "sn47.95-104:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "sn47.95-104:1.3"
msgid "Rūparāgo, arūparāgo, māno, uddhaccaṃ, avijjā—"
msgstr ""
"Desire for rebirth in the realm of luminous form, desire for rebirth in the "
"formless realm, conceit, restlessness, and ignorance."

msgctxt "sn47.95-104:1.4"
msgid "imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañcuddhambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni."
msgstr "These are the five higher fetters."

msgctxt "sn47.95-104:1.5"
msgid ""
"Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ uddhambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ abhiññāya "
"pariññāya parikkhayāya pahānāya cattāro satipaṭṭhānā bhāvetabbā."
msgstr ""
"The four kinds of mindfulness meditation should be developed for the direct "
"knowledge, complete understanding, finishing, and giving up of these five "
"higher fetters."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn47.95-104:2.1"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn47.95-104:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, "
"vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, "
"aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "sn47.95-104:2.3"
msgid "vedanāsu … pe …"
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings …"

msgctxt "sn47.95-104:2.4"
msgid "citte … pe …"
msgstr "mind …"

msgctxt "sn47.95-104:2.5"
msgid ""
"dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the "
"world."

msgctxt "sn47.95-104:2.6"
msgid ""
"Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ uddhambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ abhiññāya "
"pariññāya parikkhayāya pahānāya ime cattāro satipaṭṭhānā bhāvetabbā”ti."
msgstr ""
"These four kinds of mindfulness meditation should be developed for the "
"direct knowledge, complete understanding, finishing, and giving up of these "
"five higher fetters.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.95-104:2.7"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn47.95-104:3.1"
msgid "(Yathā maggasaṃyuttaṃ tathā satipaṭṭhānasaṃyuttaṃ vitthāretabbaṃ.)"
msgstr ""
"(The Linked Discourses on Mindfulness Meditation should be expanded as in "
"the Linked Discourses on the Path.)"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.95-104:3.2"
msgid "Oghavaggo dasamo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn47.95-104:4.1"
msgid "Ogho yogo upādānaṃ,"
msgstr "Floods, bonds, grasping,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn47.95-104:4.2"
msgid "ganthā anusayena ca;"
msgstr "ties, and underlying tendencies,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn47.95-104:4.3"
msgid "Kāmaguṇā nīvaraṇā,"
msgstr "kinds of sensual stimulation, hindrances,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn47.95-104:4.4"
msgid "khandhā oruddhambhāgiyāti."
msgstr "aggregates, and fetters high and low."

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn47.95-104:4.5"
msgid "Satipaṭṭhānasaṃyuttaṃ tatiyaṃ."
msgstr "The Linked Discourses on Mindfulness Meditation is the third section."
